title: Saints, Eagles Ready for Rivalry Renewal
text:
Saints, Eagles Ready for Rivalry Renewal 
By Zach Schneider October 15, 2015 Updated Oct 15, 2015 at 10:47 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The St. Scholastica and Northwestern football teams have become natural rivals while competing in the Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC), and that will renew itself this Saturday night. 
Both teams enter the game a perfect (5-0) in the UMAC, but St. Scholastica head coach Kurt Ramler has made his guys very aware that only one team can leave that way. 
"They're a good football team," he said, "and whoever wins this game will have an inside track to what our goals are --- winning the conference and making the national playoffs." 
The players say this has become one of the games they most look forward to every season. 
"As a senior class, we've finished 1-2 with them every single year," senior linebacker Alex Mangan said. "Every single game has been close, so we do see it as a bit of a rivalry." 
Saturday's game kicks off at 6:00 p.m. in St. Paul, Minn.
